@startuml performance-baseline-declaration-review
' Requirements: L1-QLT-002, L2-QLT-004
' Source: docs/specs/quality-and-governance/L1.md, docs/specs/quality-and-governance/L2.md
title Performance baseline declaration review (numeric targets inspection)
autonumber

actor "Baseline Reviewer" as REV
participant "Baseline Review Checklist" as CHK
database "Baseline Document Store\n(docs/specs, versioned)" as DOC

REV -> CHK ++ : Start review of active baseline revision
CHK -> DOC ++ : Fetch performance section of\nactive baseline revision
DOC --> CHK -- : performance targets section

note right of CHK
  L2-QLT-004 acceptance:
  GIVEN the active baseline revision WHEN the
  performance section is reviewed THEN each
  required metric has an explicit numeric target.
end note

loop for each required metric:\ningest rate, parameter update rate,\nend-to-end latency percentiles,\narchive write throughput
  CHK -> CHK : Verify explicit numeric target\n(value + unit + percentile where applicable)
end

alt Every required metric has a numeric target
  CHK --> REV : Inspection passed
  REV -> DOC ++ : Record inspection evidence\n(reviewer, date, revision id)
  DOC --> REV -- : evidence stored
  REV -> REV : Baseline accepted as contractual\nperformance definition (L1-QLT-002)
else A metric target is missing or non-numeric (e.g. "TBD")
  CHK --> REV -- : Inspection failed\n(list of unquantified metrics)
  REV -> REV : Reject baseline revision;\nraise action to quantify targets (TBD-013)\nbefore performance work is accepted
end

@enduml
